  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ERCP patients,

          -  Age 18-85 years old.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Coagulation dysfunction (INR&gt; 1.3) and low peripheral blood platelet count(&lt;50×109 /
             L) or using anti-coagulation drugs,

          -  Preoperative coexistent diseases: acute pancreatitis, GI tract hemorrhage, severe
             liver disease, shock, liver or kidney malfunction,

          -  Diabetes（blood glucose fluctuations）or with complications,

          -  Intestinal obstruction or other contraindications with feeding and watering,

          -  Prior surgery of Bismuth Ⅱ and Roux-en-Y,

          -  Pregnant women,

          -  Unwillingness or inability to consent for the study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
